README – Weather & Climate Analysis Project
Overview :

This project explores global weather and climate patterns through exploratory data analysis, environmental analysis, spatial visualization, and temperature forecasting.

The analysis includes:

Climate trends over time
Country-level weather comparisons
Air quality and weather relationships
Geographical temperature distribution
Temperature prediction and model evaluation


Running the Notebook :

This notebook is designed to run on Google Colab.

The dataset is loaded automatically from a public Google Drive CSV URL, so no manual dataset upload is required.

To run the project:

Open the notebook in Google Colab (Clone it from Github)
Run all cells sequentially

All required libraries are included in Google Colab by default.

What Was Done

The project involved:

1.Data cleaning and preprocessing
2.Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to identify weather and climate patterns
3.Environmental analysis to study relationships between weather variables and air quality
4.Spatial analysis to visualize temperature distribution geographically
5.Forecasting and evaluation to compare prediction performance